  "sections": {
    "Background": {
      "text": "This is the current ORS solution recommended for oral re-hydration of children and adults\nIn 2003, WHO and UNICEF recommended that the osmolarity of ORS be reduced from 311 to 245 mOsm/L .\n[1]\nNeed for unscheduled supplemental IV therapy in children given this solution was reduced by 33%",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Contents": {
      "text": "Components:\n[2]\n2.6g NaCl\n2.9g Trisodium citrate\n1.5 g KCl\n13.5 g glucose\nper 1L of water\nSodium = 75 mEq/L\nGlucose = 75 mmol/L\nTotal osmolarity = 245 mOsm/L",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
